snippet.title: 005 MONACO GRAND PRIX - Having fun while crashing | DREAMVERSE
snippet.description:
This is a video about a couple of things, but it's mostly about Monaco Grand Prix for the Sega Dreamcast.
While not having the official team licenses, and even if you lack interest in Formula 1, the driving is still fun in this game. And I want a game with just the retro races in this game.

'Dreamverse' is about chronologically talking about every European and North American released game for SEGAs last console. 

Apologies for sometimes butchering the japanese language (and other languages).

Music by
Oculus_Official - "Summer Lofi"
https://youtu.be/6xPGvz6MCwM

Classic F1 footage from ArgentinianGamer
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zv3ZxgiZTJc&t=1s

Projector sound
https://freesound.org/people/ajoyce86/sounds/212439/
